description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Highly Specialist Speech and Language Therapist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£43,712 - £49,325 per annum incl. HCAS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;West Middlesex University Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to be part of an energetic and supportive team? We are re-structuring our service and an exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced and dynamic Band 7 Speech and Language Therapist. The candidate should be someone with highly specialist clinical knowledge and skills, who is enthusiastic about service promotion and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team currently consists of 5 Speech &amp; Language Therapists, with 4 additional SLTs based at Chelsea and Westminster Hospital. The adult service offers regular site specific and full department meetings, with consistent access supervision and CPD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is based on the acute wards West Middlesex University Hospital. We are looking for someone who has experience providing clinical supervision and who has completed their videofluoroscopy and tracheostomy competencies. You will be accountable to the Clinical Lead for Adult Speech and Language Therapy at Chelsea and Westminster Hospital NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is an excellent opportunity and provides on-going opportunities for personal and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to receiving your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jessica Newman, Clinical Lead for Adult Speech and Language Therapy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;jessica.newman1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07776 317 314&lt;/p&gt;
